TETRAPOL receiver

For lisense see file COPYING.

This is set of software tool which together with SDR receiver allows:
  - find TETRAPOL control channels and identify base stations
  - TODO: recieve TETRAPOL downlink transmissions
  - TODO: detect and decode uplink transmission
  - TODO: decode recieved audio

== Installation

You need various libraries, because this software is rapidly changing, no
list is provided here. You should be able to idetify it by you-self
(try and failure method).

Use the following magic sequence to build this project.

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make

== Usage

# 1) edit ruh.sh as needed
# 2) connect SDR (RTL-SDR, BladeRF, HackRF or any supported by osmo-sdr)
# 3) run it
./run.sh

See file run.sh for example of usage. This script should give you basic
inspiration what to do and how to use this tool. If you feel totaly lost
you should try harder or start playing with something simpler.

